SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
CircuitModifier
The CircuitModifier interface represents an operation that can be applied to a quantum state vector within a quantum circuit.
CNOTGate
The CNOTGate class represents a controlled NOT gate, a two-qubit quantum gate where the target qubit is inverted if and only if the control qubit is in the state |1⟩.
CombinableCircuitModifier
The CombinableCircuitModifier interface extends CircuitModifier and represents a circuit modifier that can be combined with another CombinableCircuitModifier for circuit optimization.
ComplexMatrix
Represents a matrix of complex numbers.
ComplexNumber
Represents a complex number with real and imaginary parts.
CZGate
The CZGate class represents a controlled-Z gate, a two-qubit quantum gate that performs a conditional phase shift on the target qubit based on the state of the control qubit.
HGate
The HGate class represents a Hadamard gate, a single-qubit quantum gate that creates a superposition by putting the qubit in an equal probability of being in state |0⟩ or |1⟩.
IGate
The IGate class represents an identity gate, a single-qubit quantum gate that leaves the state of the target qubit unchanged.
Measurement
The Measurement class represents a quantum measurement operation on a single qubit.
QuantumCircuitSimulator
QuantumCircuitSimulator represents a quantum circuit simulator capable of simulating the evolution of a quantum circuit and measuring its final state.
QuantumGate
The QuantumGate class is an abstract implementation of the CombinableCircuitModifier interface, representing a quantum gate that can be applied to a quantum state vector.
RXGate
The RXGate class represents a quantum gate that performs a rotation around the X-axis in the Bloch sphere.
RYGate
The RXGate class represents a quantum gate that performs a rotation around the Y-axis in the Bloch sphere.
RZGate
The RZGate class represents a quantum gate that performs a rotation around the Z-axis in the Bloch sphere.
SGate
The SGate class represents a quantum gate applying the S (Phase) operation on a single qubit.
SparseMatrix
Represents a sparse matrix with complex number entries.
StateVector
Represents a quantum state vector, which is a mathematical entity used to describe the state of a quantum system.
SwapGate
The SwapGate class represents a quantum gate applying the SWAP operation on two qubits.
TGate
The TGate class represents a quantum gate applying the T operation on a qubit.
UncombinableCircuitModifier
The UncombinableCircuitModifier interface extends CircuitModifier and represents a circuit modifier that cannot be combined with other circuit modifiers for optimization.
UnorderedPair
Represents an unordered pair of integers.
XGate
The XGate class represents a quantum gate applying the Pauli-X (NOT) operation on a qubit.
YGate
The YGate class represents a quantum gate applying the Pauli-Y operation on a qubit.
ZGate
The ZGate class represents a quantum gate applying the Pauli-Z operation on a qubit.
